Name: AIRCRAFT TYPE
Explanation: CODES USED TO IDENTIFY SPECIFIC TYPES OF AIRCRAFT.

Explanation: THE TYPES OF HELICOPTERS, DEFINED BY THEIR LITERAL NAMES, PROVIDED BY A SPECIFIED UNIT FOR A VERTICAL REPLENISHMENT AT SEA OPERATION.

Name: AIRCRAFT IDENTIFIER
Explanation: AIRCRAFT IDENTIFICATION BY NAME, MODEL DESIGNATION, OR MARK NUMBER. RELATED DOC: AOBAC, PART 1

Name: AEW AIRCRAFT
Explanation: ALL KNOWN AIRCRAFT USED TO PERFORM EARLY WARNING MISSIONS.

Name: AIRCRAFT TYPE AND MODEL, OTHER
Explanation: THE TYPE AND MODEL NUMBER OF AN AIRCRAFT.

Name: REFUELLING AIRCRAFT TYPE
Explanation: THE KIND OF AIRCRAFT USED TO TRANSPORT AND DISPENSE FUEL TO OTHER AIRCRAFT WHILE IN FLIGHT.

Name: AIRCRAFT BY TYPE, MODEL OR CODE
LINK 4 CONTROLLED AIRCRAFT
